            "value": "<p>Your training focused on Crafting one particular kind of item. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Crafting checks to Craft woven items. If you are a master in Crafting, this bonus increases to +2.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Sample Items</strong> Textiles, baskets, and rugs</p>\n<p>If it's unclear whether the specialty applies, the GM decides. Some specialties might apply only partially. For example, if you were making a morningstar and had specialty in woodworking, the GM might give you half your bonus because the item requires both blacksmithing and woodworking.</p>"
